http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Vijayawada/NGT-directs-States-to-check-illegal-sand-mining/article13988338.ece

The National Green Tribunal (NGT) has directed the governments of Andhra Pradesh, Telangana, Maharashtra and Odisha to ensure that there is no illegal mechanised mining on the river beds without environmental clearance and the consent of the pollution control board of the respective States.The NGT on Thursday issued the orders following a petition filed by an NGO, Readiness for Empowerment through Legitimate Action (RELA). The matter is posted to February 5.The Andhra Pradesh government has sought two weeks time to file its affidavit. Both, AP and Odisha governments were given two-weeks time to submit the affidavits, according to Rela counsel Sravan Kumar. The State governments have also been asked to ensure that machines are not used in the sand mining. RELA General Secretary Konduri Ramesh Babu and Polavaram Mandal former president Vara Laxmi filed petition against the illegal sand mining activities being carried on in the riverbed of Krishna and Godavari, Tungabhadra, Pranahitha, Handri-Neeva, Manjeera, Swarnamukhi and their tributaries everyday, he said.